\subsection linear-algebra-compar Lapack performance comparison

The following table gives some results obtained on Ubuntu 18.04 with a DELL Laptop equipped with an Intel core i7-8650U CPU @ 1.90GHz that has 8 cores and 32 GB RAM. Results were obtained using:
\verbatim
$ ./perfMatrixMultiplication --benchmark --lapack-min-size 0
\endverbatim
that was build setting the appropriate `USE_BLAS/LAPACK=[ MKL | OpenBLAS | Netlib | Atlas | GSL ]` CMake option during configuration.

Moreover, when `OpenBLAS`, `Netlib` or `Atlas` were selected we used `update-alternatives` tool to select the right Lapack library using:
\verbatim
$ sudo update-alternatives --config liblapack.so.3-x86_64-linux-gnu
\endverbatim

Next table summarises the results we obtained:

